import getWeb3 from '../utils/getWeb3'

const web3 = async () => await getWeb3()

const accounts = async () => await web3.eth.getAccounts()

const kaneAcc = accounts[1]
const troutAcc = accounts[2]
const kershowAcc = accounts[3]
const johnson = accounts[4]

const Kane = {
  userBank: 'TRUFFLE',
  userName: 'Kane',
  password: '1234',
  userAddress: kaneAcc,
  balanceOf: 100000,
  transactions: []
}

const Trout = {
  userBank: 'TRUFFLE',
  userName: 'Trout',
  password: '1234',
  userAddress: troutAcc,
  balanceOf: 500000,
  transactions: []
}

const Kershow = {
  userBank: 'TRUFFLE',
  userName: 'Kershow',
  password: '1234',
  userAddress: kershowAcc,
  balanceOf: 300000,
  transactions: []
}

const Johnson = {
  userBank: 'TRUFFLE',
  userName: 'Johnson',
  password: '1234',
  userAddress: johnson,
  balanceOf: 200000,
  transactions: []
}

console.log(Johnson.userAddress)

export { accounts, Kane, Trout, Kershow, Johnson }
